#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:79
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installing and setting up &deng;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "Install the <systemitem>docker</systemitem> package:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:84
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;zypper install docker"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "To automatically start the &docker; service at boot time:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl enable docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This also automatically enables <systemitem>docker.socket</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:98
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/docker</filename> file. Search for the "
"parameter <parameter>DOCKER_OPTS</parameter> and add <literal>--insecure-"
"registry <replaceable>ADDRESS_OF_YOUR_REGISTRY</replaceable></literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:106
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Add CA certificates to the directory <filename>/etc/docker/certs.d/"
"<replaceable>REGISTRY_ADDRESS</replaceable></filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:110
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;cp CA /etc/pki/trust/anchors/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Copy the CA certificates to your system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;update-ca-certificates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the &docker; service:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl start docker.service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "This automatically starts <systemitem>docker.socket</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &docker; daemon listens on a local socket accessible only by the "
"<systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user and by the members of "
"the <systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group. The "
"<systemitem class=\"groupname\">docker</systemitem> group is automatically "
"created during package installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To allow a certain user to connect to the local &docker; daemon, use the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.sudo;/usr/sbin/usermod -aG docker <replaceable>USERNAME</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:146
#, no-c-format
msgid "This allows the user to communicate with the local &docker; daemon."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring the network"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To give the containers access to the external network, enable the "
"<option>ipv4 ip_forward</option> rule."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "How &deng; interacts with <command>iptables</command>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To learn more about how containers interact with each other and the system "
"firewall, see the <link xlink:href=\"https://docs.docker.com/v17.09/engine/"
"userguide/networking/default_network/container-communication/\">&docker; "
"documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is also possible to completely prevent &deng; from manipulating "
"<command>iptables</command> . See the <link xlink:href=\"https://docs.docker."
"com/network/iptables/#prevent-docker-from-manipulating-iptables\">&docker; "
"documentation</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage drivers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "&deng; supports different storage drivers:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">vfs</systemitem> : This driver is "
"automatically used when the &docker; host file system does not support copy-"
"on-write. This driver is simpler than the others listed and does not "
"leverage certain advantages of &deng; such as shared layers. It is a "
"reliable but slow driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">devicemapper</systemitem> : This driver "
"relies on the device-mapper thin provisioning module. It supports copy-on-"
"write, so it leverages all the advantages of &deng;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">btrfs</systemitem> : This driver relies on "
"Btrfs to provide all the features required by &deng;. To use this driver, "
"the <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> directory must be on a Btrfs file "
"system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:227
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since &productname;&nbsp;12 onward, the Btrfs file system is used by "
"default, which forces &deng; to use the <systemitem class=\"resource"
"\">btrfs</systemitem> driver."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to specify what driver to use by changing the value of the "
"<envar>DOCKER_OPTS</envar> variable defined in the <filename>/etc/sysconfig/"
"docker</filename> file. This can be done either manually or using &yast; by "
"browsing to the <menuchoice> <guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>/etc/"
"sysconfig Editor</guimenu> <guimenu>System</guimenu> <guimenu>Management</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>DOCKER_OPTS</guimenu> </menuchoice> menu and entering the "
"<systemitem class=\"library\">-s storage_driver</systemitem> string."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, to force the usage of the <systemitem class=\"resource"
"\">devicemapper</systemitem> driver, enter the following text:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "DOCKER_OPTS=\"-s devicemapper\""
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is recommended to mount <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> on a "
"separate partition or volume. In case of file system corruption, this would "
"leave the operating system running &deng; unaffected."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you choose the Btrfs file system for <filename>/var/lib/docker</"
"filename> , it is strongly recommended to create a subvolume for it. This "
"ensures that the directory is excluded from file system snapshots. If you do "
"not exclude <filename>/var/lib/docker</filename> from snapshots, the file "
"system will likely run out of disk space soon after you start deploying "
"containers. In addition, a rollback to a previous snapshot will also reset "
"the &docker; database and images. For more information, see <link xlink:href="
"\"&dsc-sles;-15/html/SLES-all/cha-snapper.html#sec-snapper-setup-customizing-"
"new-subvolume\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updates"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All updates to the <package>docker</package> package are marked as "
"interactive (that is, no automatic updates) to avoid accidental updates "
"breaking running container workloads. In general, we recommend stopping all "
"running containers before applying an update to &deng;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: containers-docker-installation.xml:281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To avoid data loss, we do not recommend having workloads rely on containers "
"being start-able after an update to &deng;. Although it is technically "
"possible to keep containers running during an update via the <option>--live-"
"restore</option> option, experience has shown that such updates can "
"introduce regressions. &suse; does not support this feature."
msgstr ""
